point blank is a 1967 american neo-noir crime film directed by john boorman , starring lee marvin , co-starring angie dickinson , keenan wynn and carroll o'connor , and adapted from the 1963 crime noir pulp novel the hunter by donald e. westlake , writing as richard stark . boorman directed the film at marvin 's request and marvin played a central role in the film 's development . the film was not a box-office success in 1967 , but has since gone on to become a cult classic , &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; praise from such critics as film historian david thomson . in 2016 , point blank was deemed " culturally , historically , or aesthetically significant " by the united states library of congress , and selected for preservation in its national film registry .